# CONSULT-39 — Why some bump draws read b0 c1/c3 = 0

## 1. `setStaticShader` dedup guard

**`Direct3d11_StateCache::setStaticShader` has no dedup.** It always calls `apply(pass)`:

```2399:2420:D:\Code\swg-client-v2\src\engine\client\application\Direct3d11\src\win32\Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp
void Direct3d11_StateCache::setStaticShader(StaticShader const &shader, int pass)
{
	// ...
	Direct3d11_StaticShaderData const * d3dShader =
		static_cast<Direct3d11_StaticShaderData const *>(shader.m_graphicsData);
	NOT_NULL(d3dShader);
	IGNORE_RETURN(d3dShader->apply(pass));
}
```

**Dedup lives in `Direct3d11_StaticShaderData::apply`:**

```762:767:D:\Code\swg-client-v2\src\engine\client\application\Direct3d11\src\win32\Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp
	bool const cacheHit = (ms_active == this && ms_activePass == passNumber);

	if (!cacheHit)
	{
		ms_active     = this;
		ms_activePass = passNumber;
```

- Compare: **`ms_active == this`** (`Direct3d11_StaticShaderData const*`) **AND** **`ms_activePass == passNumber`**.
- No dirty flag; no shader-bytecode pointer compare.
- On **`cacheHit`**, the entire `if (!cacheHit) { ... }` block (`:764`–`:1722`) is skipped: no `setCurrentVSData`/`setCurrentPSData`, no legacy-b0 staging/upload, no `writeShadowBack`, no per-pass RS/texture work.
- Cache is cleared each frame at `beginFrame()` (`:294`–`:297`).

**D3D9 has the same pattern** (`ms_active != this || ms_pass != pass`) at `Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:1047`–`:1057`; on hit it also skips `Pass::apply()` and constant uploads.

**Why this matters for buildings:** `StaticShaderTemplate::fetchShader()` returns **one shared `StaticShader` per template**:

```169:175:D:\Code\swg-client-v2\src\engine\client\library\clientGraphics\src\shared\StaticShaderTemplate.cpp
const Shader *StaticShaderTemplate::fetchShader() const
{
	if (!m_staticShader)
		m_staticShader = new StaticShader(*this);

	m_staticShader->fetch();
	return m_staticShader;
```

All building meshes using the same bump `.sht` share the same `StaticShader*` → same `Direct3d11_StaticShaderData*` → **cache hit on the 2nd+ consecutive draw** with the same pass index.

**What was last in b0 when apply is skipped?** Whatever last called `Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer::updatePS(0, ...)`. The per-primitive sorter calls **`setAlphaFadeOpacity` immediately before `setStaticShader`**:

```742:746:D:\Code\swg-client-v2\src\engine\client\library\clientGraphics\src\shared\ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp
		Graphics::setAlphaFadeOpacity(alphaFadeOpacityEnabled, alphaFadeOpacity);
		
		for (int i = 0; i < numberOfPasses; ++i)
		{
			Graphics::setStaticShader(staticShader, i);
```

`setAlphaFadeOpacity` does a **16-byte** `updatePS(0, ...)`:

```2022:2028:D:\Code\swg-client-v2\src\engine\client\application\Direct3d11\src\win32\Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp
void Direct3d11_StateCache::setAlphaFadeOpacity(bool /*enabled*/, float opacity)
{
	XMFLOAT4 fade(opacity, opacity, opacity, opacity);
	Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer::updatePS(0, &fade, sizeof(fade));
}
```

With `P19_CBUF_ZERO_TAIL`, `updatePS` **zero-fills the whole 1152-byte mapped region**, then copies only `sizeBytes`:

```208:214:D:\Code\swg-client-v2\src\engine\client\application\Direct3d11\src\win32\Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer.cpp
#if P19_CBUF_ZERO_TAIL
	std::memset(mapped.pData, 0, static_cast<size_t>(kMaxCBufferBytes));
#endif
	std::memcpy(mapped.pData, data, sizeBytes);
```

So on a cache hit: **`setAlphaFadeOpacity` zeros GPU b0 c1/c3/c4**, then **apply is skipped**, draw reads **zero dot3 diffuse/tangent** — matching locked fact #1 and #4.

D3D9 does **not** clobber PS b0 here; alpha fade is folded into `LightManager` dot3 `.a` channels (`Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:795`–`:862`), which is why D3D9 stays correct.

